We should include Actigraph as an objective measure of sleep quality.
This is a wearable device that measures physical activity, sedentary behavior, and sleep and wake activities through motion and light intensity sensors.
This data is then used to determine sleep duration and sleep efficiency (the percentage of total time in bed spent sleeping).
Actigraph has been shown to be a reliable and valid measure of sleep quality in both experimental and clinical settings, making it a suitable choice for this research.

